<Base
  title="Blind Ant | Charli-Jo Tyrer"
  description="Blind Ant is Charli-Jo Tyrer's conceptual art practice, using generative AI for design fiction, fictional systems, speculative artefacts and invented worlds."
>
  <h1>Blind Ant</h1>
  <p class="site-intro">Blind Ant is the conceptual art practice of Charli-Jo Tyrer.</p>

  <section aria-labelledby="what-is-blind-ant">
    <h2 id="what-is-blind-ant">What Blind Ant is</h2>
    <p>Blind Ant uses generative AI as an artistic medium. Its work appears through generated text, images, websites, publications and other artefacts.</p>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="design-fiction">
    <h2 id="design-fiction">Design fiction as practice</h2>
    <p>Blind Ant creates design fiction: situations, organisations, products, institutions and characters that are deliberately fictional rather than presented as operational projects.</p>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="ai-medium">
    <h2 id="ai-medium">Generative AI as medium</h2>
    <p>The authorship lies in designing concepts, systems, prompts, constraints, voices and contexts. Generative AI is one of the materials through which those choices become visible.</p>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="selected-works">
    <h2 id="selected-works">Selected worlds and works</h2>
    <p>Selected worlds, collections and fictional institutions will be gathered here as they are ready to be published.</p>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="about-artist">
    <h2 id="about-artist">About the artist</h2>
    <p>Charli-Jo Tyrer is a blind writer and conceptual artist working across accessibility, AI and speculative systems.</p>
  </section>

  <p><a href="/">Back to Charli.info</a></p>
</Base>
